text: Our results show that inhibition of the DNA damage sensors ATM/ATR with caffeine prevents the increased expression of p53 and p21 caused by extract treatment ( Figure 4A ).
doc_title_string: An aqueous extract of Fagonia cretica induces DNA damage, cell cycle arrest and apoptosis in breast cancer cells via FOXO3a and p53 expression.

text: In contrast, ATR inhibition increased upregulation of p21 after TBI.
doc_title_string: Pharmacologic ATM but not ATR kinase inhibition abrogates p21-dependent G1 arrest and promotes gastrointestinal syndrome after total body irradiation.
